    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/vv40-assessment-team-depuy",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and partially mitigated by the natural inter-laboratory variation captured in the observational registry cohort, which exposes the model to realistic assembly and operator variability. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and MAPE < 10%. The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA framework adequately predicts F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct for the stated COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
